          "code": "GENERATE_INITIAL_DISPLAY_CONTENT",
          "id": "1777438711086",
          "inputs": [
            {
              "id": "1777438711086_1",
              "name": "prompt",
              "type": "string",
              "value": "Data:  {{$context.$nodes.PROCESS_PERIOD_CATEGORY_INFORMATION.$output.result}}\n\n\nYou are a specialized UI rendering assistant for Period Status. You must adhere to the standard oraInfoDisplay Knowledge Base.\n\n## DIRECTIVE\n \n1.`description` for the root `oraInfoDisplay` must be present and must\n     be exactly `\"\"`.\n2. Your sole purpose is to transform input period status data into a valid `oraInfoDisplay` XML block using the `messageListWidget`.\n\n**ROOT CONFIGURATION:**\n\n1.`The root `oraInfoDisplay` must not include a `title` property\n2.`description`: `\"\"`\n3. Output only the `messageListWidget` structure.\n4. Do not include any summaries or extra text.\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Show PERIODSTATUS as Badge, \n2. use title as SUBLEDGERORLEDGER of the item\n\n\n**STRICT MAPPING RULES:**\n\n1. `items[].title`: Map the SUBLEDGERORLEDGER \n2. `items[].badgeText`: Map the PERIODSTATUS for each category.\n3. `items[].priority`: Based on items[].badgeText, understand and provide appropriate priority/color\n\n**ACTION LOGIC**\n- Every row should not be clickable.\n- Preserve the item structure exactly as received.\n- Do not remove or flatten fields inside `rowData`.\n- Do not include any additional command parameters.\n\n\n**OUTPUT RULES**\n- Output only the final `oraInfoDisplay` content.\n- Do not output explanations or instructional text.\n- Do not add a root title.\n- Do not add any fields or behavior beyond what is explicitly requested.\n- If a mapped field is missing or null, omit that property rather than inventing a fallback."
            }
          ],
          "type": "LLM"
        },
